sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor LLM as LLM requester
  actor User
  participant API as Promotion API
  participant Orchestrator as Promotion orchestrator
  participant Git as Repo and dev/main
  participant Scripts as Existing deterministic scripts
  participant Prod as PROD backend
  participant Actions as GitHub Actions
  participant Releases as Release and update registry
  participant Evidence as Promotion evidence store

  LLM->>API: promotion.run(source=dev/main,target=prod,release_android=true)
  API->>Orchestrator: Validate parameters and create run
  Orchestrator->>Git: Check branch, clean trees, tags, and merge evidence
  Orchestrator->>Scripts: Run SDD doctor and release-network checks
  Orchestrator->>Evidence: Store preflight and validation logs
  Orchestrator-->>User: Request approval with exact release plan
  User->>Orchestrator: Approve
  Orchestrator->>Prod: Enable drain and wait for active jobs
  Orchestrator->>Scripts: safe_restart_backend.sh
  Scripts->>Prod: Restart and health check
  Orchestrator->>Actions: Trigger Android release workflow
  Actions->>Releases: Publish PROD and DEV channel APKs
  Orchestrator->>Scripts: validate_backend_post_release.sh
  Orchestrator->>Releases: Validate updater metadata and app identities
  Orchestrator->>Evidence: Store tags, URLs, logs, validation, rollback hints
  Orchestrator-->>API: done, blocked, or failed
  API-->>LLM: Structured result only

  Note over LLM,API: LLM never receives shell, git, restart, or deploy command execution.

